msgid "Searching Hints"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: content/en/search/searchhints.adoc:8
#, no-wrap
msgid "If you got lots of irrelevant results..."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/search/searchhints.adoc:11
msgid ""
"If you search for several words such as \"quantum hard drives\", an OR is "
"implied meaning that to be counted as relevant, only one of the words has to "
"appear in a message. To find only messages with all three words, change the "
"search to \"quantum and hard and drives\""
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/search/searchhints.adoc:12
msgid ""
"If you still get lots of irrelevant messages, see if they have something in "
"common. If so, you can exclude them with the *not* operator. For example "
"\"quantum and hard and drives not ide\" will exclude any messages about ide "
"quantum hard drives."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: content/en/search/searchhints.adoc:13
#, no-wrap
msgid "If you do not think you received everything you should have..."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/search/searchhints.adoc:16
msgid ""
"If one of your keywords has variant forms, be sure to enter all relevant "
"forms. If you are searching for \"buslogic\", you might change it to "
"\"buslogic or bustek\"."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/search/searchhints.adoc:17
msgid ""
"Words with varying suffixes can be wildcarded. Searching for \"drive*\" will "
"pick up words such as drive, drives, driver, drivers and so on."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/search/searchhints.adoc:18
msgid ""
"Try discarding words that could be implied by the context of the "
"message. For example \"quantum and hard and drive\" might miss some relevant "
"messages that \"quantum and drive\" would get."
msgstr ""

